records.englishTranslation:
SERVET MULLAOĞLU (Hatay) - Thank you, Mr. President.
Many neighborhoods of Hatay Reyhanlı district have been established on lands without title deeds for sixty or seventy years. Citizens living in those neighborhoods are not given electricity subscriptions, and high fines are imposed instead. Even the Üçtepe Neighborhood Mosque was not given any subscriptions, and high fines were even imposed on the mosque. One of the biggest bleeding wounds of our Reyhanlı district is the problem of not providing electricity subscription. Many of our citizens are forced to survive in primitive conditions. Living a life worthy of human dignity is one of the fundamental human rights. Electricity is one of the important elements that affects life in every aspect of life;
For this reason, we kindly request, on behalf of the people of Reyhanlı, that first of all, our citizens be given the electricity subscription of the places where they live, and then the title deeds of the lands where they live are given. (From CHP ranks
